‚ÄºÔ∏è‚ÄºÔ∏è Missouri Attorney General, 76 Parents File Suit Against 45 School Districts to Halt Mask Mandates

January 25, 2022
Contact: Constituent Services
Office: 573-751-3321

JEFFERSON CITY, Mo. ‚Äì  The Missouri Attorney General Eric Schmitt, along with 76 parents as plaintiffs in certain cases, filed separate lawsuits against 45 school districts across the state to halt those districts from illegally enforcing mask mandates. Districts sued today are Francis Howell, Park Hill, Columbia, Fort Zumwalt, Lee‚Äôs Summit, Holden, Affton, Liberty, Jefferson City, St. Charles, Kansas City, Waynesville, Hazelwood, Raytown, Kingsville, Rockwood, Hickman Mills, Ladue, Center, Dunklin R-V, Independence, Lindbergh, Grandview, Fox C-6, North Kansas City, Ferguson-Florissant, Maplewood, Clayton, St. Louis City, Parkway, Brentwood, Valley Park, Pattonville, Webster Groves, Mehlville, Warrensburg, Bayless, Jennings, Lexington, Kirkwood, Ritenour, Hancock Place, Special School District of St. Louis, Meramec Valley, and University City.

Last month, following a recent Cole County ruling, the Attorney General‚Äôs Office opened up an inbox for parents to report non-compliant districts. The Office has since received over 11,000 email submissions to that inbox, and has sent a number of school districts to non-compliant school districts. Some have dropped their mask mandates, but others have continued to defy the law.

‚ÄúMask mandates in schools are illegal, they simply don‚Äôt work, and they contribute to alarming and negative psychological impacts on our children. My Office has been on the frontlines of the fight to end the forced masking of children all day in school, and today we took concrete legal action toward that end,‚Äù said Attorney General Schmitt. ‚ÄúParents and families, not bureaucrats, should have the power to decide what‚Äôs best for their children. With this litigation, we‚Äôre seeking to return that power back to parents and families, where it belongs.‚Äù

The Missouri Attorney General‚Äôs Office is working with several private attorneys who are offering pro-bono legal services to parents to ensure they have a voice in this critical litigation, including Stanley B. Cox, Jennifer M. Cross, and Mark C. Milton.
